<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Description</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
(Fig. 10A). Encrusting sponge, agglutinating and consolidating limestone fragments (dead corallines and serpulids), pale yellow-coloured, with cartilaginous consistency. Growing together with a yellow-coloured 
<taxonomicName class="Demospongiae" family="Coelosphaeridae" genus="Chaetodoryx" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chaetodoryx" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">Chaetodoryx</taxonomicName>
sp. Size of agglutinated mass approx. 4
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2 cm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Skeleton: a confused mass of dichocalthrops with a thin crust of sanidasters.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Spicules: dichocalthrops (no calthrops), sanidasters.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Dichocalthrops (Fig. 10B) relatively large, regularly shaped, with limited size variation, protocladi more or less uniform in smaller and larger spicules, but deuterocladi longer in larger ones: protocladi 42
<normalizedToken originalValue="–48.2–">-48.2-</normalizedToken>
56 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
9
<normalizedToken originalValue="–21.6–">-21.6-</normalizedToken>
35 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, deuterocladi 23
<normalizedToken originalValue="–106.8–">-106.8-</normalizedToken>
204 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4
<normalizedToken originalValue="–17.2–">-17.2-</normalizedToken>
29 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, rhabdomes 71
<normalizedToken originalValue="–170.6–">-170.6-</normalizedToken>
252 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
8
<normalizedToken originalValue="–21.0–">-21.0-</normalizedToken>
31 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, cladomes 132
<normalizedToken originalValue="–294.6–">-294.6-</normalizedToken>
475 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Sanidasters relatively small, little variation in spination and ornamentation, 11
<normalizedToken originalValue="–13.3–">-13.3-</normalizedToken>
16 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
